                    An ESP32 handles all mission-critical work in
                    <strong class="text-ink-soft">no_std Rust</strong>, ADCS on CPU1,
                    comms scheduling on CPU0, with a hardware watchdog chip monitoring liveness.
                    The current simplification path is to keep imagery on the ESP32 using a camera
                    module that can emit JPEG frames directly, then store and chunk those images for
                    RF downlink. A Raspberry Pi Zero 2W remains under evaluation only as a secondary
                    camera computer, watchdogged by the ESP32 ULP if it is used.
                </p>


