                <p class="text-ink-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6 text-justify">
                    The communications baseline has moved away from LoRa/SX radios and toward a
                    flight-proven UHF GMSK transceiver for heartbeats, telemetry, commands, and
                    image chunks. SatNOGS provides the primary public downlink path, with partner
                    ground-station support under evaluation. First-contact Doppler handling starts
                    with catalog TLEs when available; if not, SatNOGS range searching and FFT
                    centroid analysis of heartbeat waveforms can recover the orbit for later passes.
                    A compact omnidirectional antenna design is being evaluated for structure-level
                    integration near the transceiver.
                </p>


