                <p class="text-ink-muted text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6 text-justify">
                    Master power from a 4P3S pack of twelve 21700-format Li-ion cells
                    stepped down to a 5 V satellite bus. Twelve 10x10 cm solar panels
                    (three per long face) both charge the pack and serve as coarse sun sensors
                    via shunt-resistor current measurement. A custom relay-based power
                    controller enforces priority-ranked load shedding under low-battery conditions.
                    Kapton tape and aluminized thermal blanketing insulate the battery from
                    orbital temperature extremes.
                </p>


