                    <h3 class="font-display text-3xl font-light text-ink mb-3">
                        Testing the EKF before the first orbit
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-ink-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
                        ADCS routines are validated pre-flight in a
                        <strong class="text-ink-soft">Basilisk</strong> astrodynamics simulation,
                        a high-performance C++ engine with Python bindings.
                        Simulation nodes exchange satellite attitude/orbit state and raw virtual
                        sensor data over <strong class="text-ink-soft">Zenoh</strong>,
                        a publish-subscribe protocol.
                        The control interface accepts <code class="text-ink-soft font-mono">applyTorque</code>
                        and <code class="text-ink-soft font-mono">applyMagneticDipole</code> commands,
                        allowing the complete EKF pipeline to be stress-tested against simulated sensor
                        noise and disturbance torques long before any hardware leaves the ground.
                    </p>
